com.netflix.zeno.serializer
Class NFTypeSerializer<T>

java.lang.Object
  com.netflix.zeno.serializer.NFTypeSerializer<T>
Type Parameters:
T - - The type of object this serializer serializes
Direct Known Subclasses:
BooleanSerializer, ByteArraySerializer, DateSerializer, EnumSerializer, IntegerSerializer, ListSerializer, LongSerializer, MapSerializer, SetSerializer, SortedMapSerializer, StringSerializer
public abstract class NFTypeSerializer<T>
extends java.lang.Object

The NFTypeSerializer is used to represent a hierarchy of Objects contained in a POJO Object model.

Using a set of NFTypeSerializers to define an Object hierarchy allows for the definition of semantically and structurally independent operations over that data. Check out the Zeno documentation section defining an object model for details about how to define your data model with NFTypeSerializers.
